overview: The user initiated a project to build a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application, focusing on database integration and an admin dashboard. The
  agent evaluated the existing codebase, identified missing features, and
  developed a comprehensive plan. Key decisions included using NeonDB
  (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for the database and implementing a simple
  password-based authentication for the admin dashboard. Initially, a custom
  session management system was built, but upon user inquiry, it was refactored
  to leverage Next.js middleware for a more streamlined and integrated approach
  to route protection. The implementation covered updating demographics,
  creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses, developing API endpoints
  for data submission and retrieval (including CSV export), and building the
  admin login and dashboard pages. The agent also provided detailed instructions
  for database setup and successfully tested the entire flow, from questionnaire
  submission to admin access and data verification.
